import matplotlib.pyplot as plt
np.random.seed(123)

dimensions={}
for i in range(1,16):
    dimensions[i]=np.random.rand(1000,i)*2-1
In [3]:
dist={}
for n in range(1,len(dimensions)+1):
    dist[n]=np.sqrt(np.sum(dimensions[n]**2, axis=1))
In [4]:
fractions={}
for f in range(1,len(dimensions)+1):
    fractions[f]=np.sum(dist[f]<1)/1000

dimensions={}

In [20]:
test_dim={}
for j in range(1,16):
    test_dim[j]=np.random.rand(100,j)*2-1
In [22]:
def nearest_neighbor (dimensions, test_dim):
    dist=np.sqrt(np.sum((dimensions-test_dim)**2, axis=1))
    return np.min(dist)
In [23]:
a=[]
mean_values={}
for n in dimensions:
    for m in range(100):
        a.append(nearest_neighbor(dimensions[n], test_dim[n][m]))
    mean_values[n]=np.mean(a)
In [25]:
plt.plot(*zip(*sorted(mean_values.items())))
plt.xlabel("sample size")
plt.ylabel("average distance")
plt.grid()
plt.show()
